  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "aFUriDSDlQjatLXBGr/FUJEczKA=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:43.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Stamp-cost accounting for `RedundancyLevel.MEDIUM`\n\nThe tradeoff is write-side, not read-side:\n\n- **Stamp usage per write goes up ~25%**: MEDIUM adds ~1 parity chunk per 4 data chunks.\n- **Op-batches (~1KB) still fit in one SOC**, so the overhead is negligible for `collab-ops-feed.ts:138`.\n- **Larger chunks** (drive share bundle, manifest snapshots) see meaningful additional stamp consumption.\n- **Reader side: zero runtime cost** if chunks arrive \u2014 redundancy is only consulted on miss/timeout.\n\n**Required code change:** our existing stamp-utilization logic calls `calculateSize` / `calculateRemainingSize(encryption, ...)`. To report honest headroom, we must thread the `redundancyLevel` parameter through these calls: `calculateRemainingSize(true, MEDIUM)` rather than just `calculateRemainingSize(true)`.\n\n**Rollback rule from the experiment plan:** if stamp-utilization chirps warn of exhaustion, back off to `OFF` for ops and keep `MEDIUM` only for long-lived bundles.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:43.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:43.000Z"
    }
  },
